subSubSection.paragraph:
Status and Conservation.
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red Lust. Brock’s Yellow-eared Bat is locally rare—a trend that has been demonstrated by its low capture frequencies in places with high netting efforts. It has been recorded in areas with conservation units with total or partial protection from, for example, bauxite extraction (e.g. Saraca-Taquera National Forest in northern Para, 
Brazil
) and iron mining (e.g. Carajas National Forest in eastern Para, 
Brazil
).
